,"attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"delegationOfFunctions","id":"idb8256c9e-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Delegation of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions of President under subsec. (b)(1) of this section delegated to Office of Personnel Management, see section 401(a) of Ex. Ord. No. 11348, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-04-20"},"text":"Apr. 20, 1967","children":[],"tail":", 32 F.R. 6335, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s4103"},"text":"section 4103 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"executiveOrder","id":"idb8256c9f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Ex. Ord. No. 10805. Central Intelligence Agency","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Ex. Ord. No. 10805, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-02-18"},"text":"Feb. 18, 1959","children":[],"tail":", 24 F.R. 1301, provided:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Section","children":[],"tail":" 1. The Central Intelligence Agency is hereby designated as excepted from the following-described provisions of the Government Employees Training Act [this chapter and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s1308"},"text":"section 1308 of this title","children":[],"tail":"]:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(a) Section 2(4), 6, 9(b)(1), 11, 12, 15, 16, and 18 [sections 4117, 4118, 4105(b)(1), 4108, 4106, 4114, 4115, and 1308(a)(4)(A)–(C), (b) and 4113(b) respectively of this title].","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(b) The last sentence of section 5 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s4113/a"},"text":"section 4113(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"]."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(c) That part of section 7 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s4103/1"},"text":"section 4103(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":"] which reads “shall conform, on or after the effective date of the regulations prescribed by the Commission under section 6 of this Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s4118"},"text":"section 4118 of this title","children":[],"tail":"], to the principles, standards, and related requirements contained in such regulations then current,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(d) That part of section 10 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s4109/a"},"text":"section 4109(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"] which reads “in accordance with regulations issued by the Commission under authority of section 6(a)(8) ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s4118/a/8"},"text":"section 4118(a)(8) of this title","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Sec","children":[],"tail":". 2. Section 2 of Executive Order No. 10800, of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-01-15"},"text":"January 15, 1959","children":[],"tail":", is hereby amended by deleting the reference to “section 5” and the reference to “section 5(b)” and by inserting in lieu thereof “section 4” and “section 4(b)”, respectively."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"executiveOrder","id":"idb8256ca0-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Order No. 11531","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Ex. Ord. No. 11531, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-05-26"},"text":"May 26, 1970","children":[],"tail":", 35 F.R. 8337, which related to the delegation of Presidential authority to designate United States Marshals and United States Attorneys for training, was superseded by Ex. Ord. No. 11895, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-01-06"},"text":"Jan. 6, 1976","children":[],"tail":", 41 F.R. 1465, set out below."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"executiveOrder","id":"idb827dca1-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Ex. Ord. No. 11895. Delegation of Presidential Authority To Designate Individuals Appointed by the President To Receive Training","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Ex. Ord. No. 11895, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-01-06"},"text":"Jan. 6, 1976","children":[],"tail":", 41 F.R. 1465, as amended by Ex. Ord. No. 12107, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-12-28"},"text":"Dec. 28, 1978","children":[],"tail":", 44 F.R. 1055, provided:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"By virtue of the authority vested in me by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t3/s301"},"text":"Section 301 of Title 3","children":[],"tail":" of the United States Code, and as President of the United States, it is hereby ordered as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Section","children":[],"tail":" 1. Except as provided in Section 2 of this Order, the Office of Personnel Management is hereby designated and empowered to exercise the authority vested in the President by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s4102/a/2/B"},"text":"Section 4102(a)(2)(B) of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, to designate individuals appointed by the President for training under Chapter 41 of Title 5, United States Code."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Sec","children":[],"tail":". 2. The Attorney General is hereby designated and empowered to exercise the authority vested in the President by Section 4102(a)(2)(B) to designate individuals appointed by the President as United States Attorneys and United States Marshals for training under Chapter 41 of Title 5, United States Code."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Sec","children":[],"tail":". 3. Executive Order No. 11531 of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-05-26"},"text":"May 26, 1970","children":[],"tail":", is hereby superseded."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
